</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_96" id="48r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Den von Costencz </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde,</ex></expan> wir <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wol
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nom<ex>en</ex></expan>, wie daz
                                <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>heilig<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>vatt<ex>er</ex></expan>, babst <expan>Joh<ex>an</ex>es,</expan> vil
                        cardinal und auch <expan>and<ex>er</ex>r</expan>
<expan>h<ex>e</ex>rschaft</expan> bey ewch zu Costencz sein und daz der
                                <expan>all<ex>er</ex></expan> durlewchtigst fürst und
                                <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>
<expan>h<ex>e</ex>r</expan>
<expan>Sig<ex>mund</ex></expan>, <expan>römisch<ex>er</ex></expan> und zu
                                <expan>Ung<ex>er</ex>n</expan> etc. künig,
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gnedigst<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re,</expan> kürczlich zu ewch gen Costenz
                                <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> well. Also
                            <expan>bitt<ex>en</ex></expan> wir ewr
                            <expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan> mit ganczem fleisz, daz ir uns bey
                        disem <expan>bott<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>schreiben</expan> wellet, wie sie die
                                <expan>ordnu<ex>n</ex>g</expan> des
                                <expan>co<ex>n</ex>ciliu<ex>m</ex>s</expan>
<expan>angefang<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> und <expan>halt<ex>en</ex></expan> und auch ob
                        ir icht <expan>and<ex>er</ex>r</expan> lewff <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan>
                        mer west, die uns zu <expan>verschr<ex>eiben</ex></expan> sein, als vil ewch
                        des denn gebüre, uns zu <expan>verschreibe<ex>n</ex></expan>,
                                <expan>sunderl<ex>ich</ex></expan> wenn der
                                <expan>vorg<ex>enante</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gnedig<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re,</expan> der <expan>r<ex>ömisch</ex></expan>
<expan>k<ex>ünig</ex></expan>, zu ewch gen Costencz
                            <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan>, daz ir uns das zu stund bey ewrselbs
                                <expan>bott<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>schreibt</expan>, das bottenlon wir
                            <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> beczaln <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, und
                        uns in den <expan>sach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> ewr
                            <expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan> und guten
                            <expan>will<ex>e</ex>n</expan> beweisen wellet, als wir
                                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>weish<ex>eit</ex></expan> etc. Das <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                        umb ewr <expan>ersamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> ii<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan>
<expan>Kath<ex>er</ex>ine.</expan>
</ab>
